---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SEO from '../../components/SEO.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - MW Design Studio">
  <SEO 
    title="Terms of Service - MW Design Studio"
    description="MW Design Studio's terms of service. Learn about our service agreements, intellectual property rights, and terms for using our design and marketing services."
    keywords="terms of service, service agreement, legal terms, intellectual property, user agreement"
  />
  
  <main>
    <section class="hero-section">
      <div class="container">
        <nav class="breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> > Terms of Service
        </nav>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="lead">Terms and conditions for using our services</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2025</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="terms-content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="terms-text">
          <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>By accessing MW Design Studio's website, engaging our services, or entering into a service agreement with us, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use our services.</p>
          
          <p>These Terms constitute a legally binding agreement between you ("Client," "you," or "your") and MW Design Studio ("MW Design Studio," "we," "us," or "our").</p>

          <h2>2. Services Overview</h2>
          <p>MW Design Studio provides professional design, marketing, and social media services, including but not limited to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Brand identity design and development</li>
            <li>Logo design and visual identity systems</li>
            <li>Marketing strategy and campaign development</li>
            <li>Social media management and content creation</li>
            <li>Email marketing and automation</li>
            <li>Consulting and strategic guidance</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Specific services, deliverables, timelines, and pricing are outlined in individual project proposals and service agreements.</p>

          <h2>3. Service Agreements and Project Scope</h2>
          
          <h3>Project Proposals</h3>
          <p>All projects begin with a detailed proposal that includes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Scope of work and deliverables</li>
            <li>Project timeline and milestones</li>
            <li>Pricing and payment terms</li>
            <li>Revision policies and limitations</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Changes to Project Scope</h3>
          <p>Any changes to the agreed-upon scope of work must be:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Requested in writing (email accepted)</li>
            <li>Approved by both parties before implementation</li>
            <li>Documented with updated timeline and costs</li>
            <li>Subject to additional fees for extra work</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Client Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>To ensure successful project completion, clients agree to:</p>
          
          <h3>Information and Materials</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide accurate, complete information during the discovery phase</li>
            <li>Supply necessary materials, content, and assets in a timely manner</li>
            <li>Ensure all provided content is original or properly licensed</li>
            <li>Obtain necessary approvals and permissions for use of materials</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Communication and Feedback</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Respond to requests for feedback within agreed timeframes</li>
            <li>Provide specific, actionable feedback on deliverables</li>
            <li>Attend scheduled meetings and check-ins</li>
            <li>Designate a primary point of contact for the project</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. Payment Terms</h2>
          
          <h3>Payment Schedule</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Standard Projects:</strong> 50% deposit upon agreement signing, 50% upon project completion</li>
            <li><strong>Large Projects:</strong> May be broken into milestone-based payments</li>
            <li><strong>Ongoing Services:</strong> Monthly billing in advance</li>
            <li><strong>Rush Projects:</strong> Full payment required upfront</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Payment Methods</h3>
          <p>We accept payment via bank transfer, check, and major credit cards. All payments are processed securely through third-party providers.</p>

          <h3>Late Payments</h3>
          <p>Payments not received within 30 days of the due date may be subject to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Late fees of 1.5% per month on outstanding balances</li>
            <li>Suspension of work until payment is received</li>
            <li>Collection agency referral for significantly overdue accounts</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>6. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
          
          <h3>Work Product Ownership</h3>
          <p>Upon full payment, clients receive ownership of:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Final deliverables specifically created for the client</li>
            <li>Custom designs, logos, and brand elements</li>
            <li>Final versions of marketing materials and content</li>
          </ul>

          <p>MW Design Studio retains ownership of:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Preliminary concepts, sketches, and work-in-progress materials</li>
            <li>Proprietary methodologies, processes, and templates</li>
            <li>Pre-existing intellectual property and tools</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Portfolio and Marketing Rights</h3>
          <p>MW Design Studio reserves the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Display completed work in our portfolio and marketing materials</li>
            <li>Use project details as case studies (with client approval)</li>
            <li>Reference client relationships in business development activities</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Third-Party Materials</h3>
          <p>When third-party materials (stock photos, fonts, etc.) are used:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Licensing costs are typically included in project pricing</li>
            <li>Clients receive appropriate usage rights as specified in licenses</li>
            <li>Extended or exclusive licensing may incur additional costs</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>7. Revisions and Approval Process</h2>
          
          <h3>Revision Allowances</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Brand Projects:</strong> 3 rounds of revisions included</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing Campaigns:</strong> 2 rounds of revisions included</li>
            <li><strong>Social Media Content:</strong> 2 rounds of revisions included</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Additional Revisions</h3>
          <p>Revisions beyond the included allowance are billed at our standard hourly rate. Significant changes that alter the project scope may require a new agreement.</p>

          <h3>Final Approval</h3>
          <p>Client approval is required before proceeding to the next project phase. Lack of response within 7 business days constitutes approval to proceed.</p>

          <h2>8. Project Timelines and Delays</h2>
          
          <h3>Timeline Commitments</h3>
          <p>We strive to meet all agreed-upon deadlines. Timelines may be adjusted due to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Delayed client feedback or material provision</li>
            <li>Significant scope changes or additional revision requests</li>
            <li>Unforeseen circumstances or force majeure events</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Client-Caused Delays</h3>
          <p>If project delays are caused by client actions or inactions:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Timeline will be adjusted accordingly</li>
            <li>Additional costs may apply for extended project management</li>
            <li>MW Design Studio is not liable for missed deadlines or launch dates</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>9. Warranties and Limitations</h2>
          
          <h3>Service Warranties</h3>
          <p>MW Design Studio warrants that our services will be:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Performed in a professional and workmanlike manner</li>
            <li>Delivered according to the agreed specifications</li>
            <li>Free from defects in materials and workmanship</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Limitation of Liability</h3>
          <p>MW Design Studio's liability is limited to the total amount paid for services. We are not liable for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Indirect, consequential, or punitive damages</li>
            <li>Lost profits or business opportunities</li>
            <li>Third-party claims or intellectual property disputes</li>
            <li>Results or performance of marketing campaigns</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>10. Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>MW Design Studio agrees to maintain the confidentiality of:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Proprietary business information shared during projects</li>
            <li>Strategic plans and competitive information</li>
            <li>Personal data and sensitive client information</li>
            <li>Unpublished work and concepts</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Confidentiality obligations survive project completion and contract termination.</p>

          <h2>11. Termination</h2>
          
          <h3>Termination by Client</h3>
          <p>Clients may terminate projects at any time with written notice. Upon termination:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Client pays for all work completed to the termination date</li>
            <li>Client receives work-in-progress materials at MW Design Studio's discretion</li>
            <li>No refunds are provided for work already completed</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Termination by MW Design Studio</h3>
          <p>We may terminate projects if:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Client breaches payment obligations</li>
            <li>Client fails to provide necessary materials or feedback</li>
            <li>Project becomes commercially unfeasible</li>
            <li>Client breaches these Terms of Service</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>12. Dispute Resolution</h2>
          <p>In the event of disputes, parties agree to:</p>
          <ol>
            <li>First attempt resolution through direct negotiation</li>
            <li>Engage in mediation if negotiation fails</li>
            <li>Resort to binding arbitration for unresolved disputes</li>
            <li>Submit to jurisdiction of [Your State/Country] courts if necessary</li>
          </ol>

          <h2>13. General Provisions</h2>
          
          <h3>Governing Law</h3>
          <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of [Your State/Country], without regard to conflict of law principles.</p>

          <h3>Force Majeure</h3>
          <p>Neither party is liable for delays or failures due to circumstances beyond their reasonable control, including natural disasters, government actions, or pandemic-related restrictions.</p>

          <h3>Severability</h3>
          <p>If any provision of these Terms is found invalid or unenforceable, the remainder of the Terms will continue in full force and effect.</p>

          <h3>Entire Agreement</h3>
          <p>These Terms, together with individual project agreements, constitute the entire agreement between the parties and supersede all prior negotiations or agreements.</p>

          <h2>14. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>MW Design Studio may update these Terms to reflect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Changes in business practices or services</li>
            <li>Legal or regulatory requirements</li>
            <li>Industry best practices</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Updated Terms will be posted on our website with a revised "Last updated" date. Continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of updated Terms.</p>

          <h2>15. Contact Information</h2>
          <p>For questions about these Terms or our services, contact us:</p>
          
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p><strong>MW Design Studio</strong></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:legal@mwdesignstudio.com">legal@mwdesignstudio.com</a></p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:+1234567890">(123) 456-7890</a></p>
            <p>Address: [Your Business Address]</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="terms-sidebar">
          <div class="quick-links">
            <h3>Quick Links</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#acceptance">Acceptance of Terms</a></li>
              <li><a href="#services">Services Overview</a></li>
              <li><a href="#payment">Payment Terms</a></li>
              <li><a href="#intellectual">Intellectual Property</a></li>
              <li><a href="#revisions">Revisions Process</a></li>
              <li><a href="#termination">Termination</a></li>
              <li><a href="#contact">Contact Information</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="help-box">
            <h3>Questions?</h3>
            <p>Need clarification on our terms?</p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
          </div>

          <div class="related-links">
            <h3>Related</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="/legal/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
              <li><a href="/faq">FAQ</a></li>
              <li><a href="/process">Our Process</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-section {
    background: var(--gradient-purple-pink);
    color: white;
    padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .last-updated {
    opacity: 0.8;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .terms-content {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  .terms-text {
    max-width: none;
  }

  .terms-text h2 {
    color: var(--accent-purple);
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--gray-100);
  }

  .terms-text h2:first-child {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .terms-text h3 {
    color: #333;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .terms-text p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #555;
  }

  .terms-text ul,
  .terms-text ol {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .terms-text li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #555;
  }

  .contact-info {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .contact-info a {
    color: var(--accent-purple);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .contact-info a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .terms-sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 2rem;
    align-self: start;
  }

  .quick-links,
  .help-box,
  .related-links {
    background: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .quick-links h3,
  .help-box h3,
  .related-links h3 {
    color: var(--accent-purple);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .quick-links ul,
  .related-links ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .quick-links li,
  .related-links li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .quick-links a,
  .related-links a {
    color: #555;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }

  .quick-links a:hover,
  .related-links a:hover {
    background: #f0f4ff;
    color: var(--accent-purple);
  }

  .help-box p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #666;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--accent-purple);
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: center;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--accent-purple);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    
    .terms-sidebar {
      position: static;
    }
    
    .quick-links {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>